word_group.brief_definition: 具备资格；有资格；获得资格

bilingual.source: He passed the exam to qualify for college.
bilingual.target: 他通过了考试，取得资格进入大学。

bilingual.source: She worked hard to qualify for the competition.
bilingual.target: 她努力工作以取得资格参加比赛。

bilingual.source: You need more experience to qualify for this job.
bilingual.target: 你需要更多的经验才能取得资格申请这个职位。

bilingual.source: They must complete the training course to qualify.
bilingual.target: 他们必须完成培训课程才能取得资格。

bilingual.source: Only eligible individuals can qualify for the grant.
bilingual.target: 只有符合条件的人才能取得资格获得补助。

bilingual.source: Where are you going to work when you qualify?
bilingual.target: 取得资格后,你打算在那工作?

bilingual.source: She worked hard to qualify for the national team.
bilingual.target: 她努力训练以使具有资格进入国家队。
某些慈善捐款符合免税额的条件。

bilingual.source: This experience will help you qualify for a higher position.
bilingual.target: 这段经历将帮助你使具有资格获得更高职位。

bilingual.source: The course is designed to qualify students for professional careers.
bilingual.target: 该课程旨在使具有资格学生从事专业职业。

yingyinNormal.en: And that doesn't even qualify as futile.
Odds are, you'll qualify for tax credits to help you afford it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很可能,你符合税收减免的条件,可以帮助你负担起这一支出。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, based on what I've heard, you two certainly don't qualify for an annulment.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从刚才的话听来，两位不符合注销资格。

yingyinNormal.en: You paid that? Free trial. I took the test to see if I qualify for the free trial.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你付款了吗？免费试听，我做了测试，看看我符不符合免费试听资格。

yingyinNormal.en: Please, anybody. I need one more monster. Just one more! Yeah, sorry. Doesn't look good. We have to move on. Your team doesn't qualify.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，我只差一个怪兽，只差一个。抱歉，情况不妙，我们得继续，你的队伍资格不符。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, while this may not qualify as statecraft, it does illustrate my effectiveness, the same effectiveness I plan on bringing to the United Nations.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虽然算不上治国才能，但也表明了我的能力，我也希望在联合国发挥我的能力。

yingyinNormal.en: It means being able to own your home, raise your children in a safe neighborhood, send them to a good school, where if they do well they can qualify to go to college.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作为中产阶级应该有自己的住房，社区安宁，有能力抚养并供孩子们上学接受良好教育。

word_usage.usage:
qualify为及物动词，qualify sb. for sth.表示“使某人具备做某事的资格”。例：
The test qualifies you to drive heavy vehicles.
通过这一考试就有资格驾驶重型车辆。

qualify与介词as连用，表示“有条件/资格做……”。例：
He qualified as a doctor last year.
他去年获得了医生的资格。

qualify的过去分词qualified可用作形容词，在句中作定语或表语，表示“具备学历/资历的”。例：
a qualified accountant/teacher
取得执业资格的会计师、教师

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。
